   <body>
      <p>The <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> block enables you to update a default value for a field in the current form. This block is available on all events except <uicontrol>After Save</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Workflow Action Complete</uicontrol>. However, the available options in <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> block are different for <uicontrol>Modify Form</uicontrol> event when compared to <uicontrol>Load Form</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Before Save</uicontrol> events.</p>
      <p>In the <uicontrol>Modify Form</uicontrol> event, you can select any of the following <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> block options as applicable: <ul>
            <li outputclass="break_avoid">From the drop-down list of <uicontrol>Set Hidden</uicontrol> field, you can select the  field name that must be hidden or available, and then update the value as <msgph>true</msgph> or <msgph>false</msgph> in the adjacent field as applicable.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Set_Hidden_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li outputclass="break_avoid">From the drop-down list of <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> field, you can select the field name that must be set to read only.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Set_ReadOnly_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li outputclass="break_avoid">From the drop-down list of <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> field, you can select the field name that must be set to mandatory.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Set_Mandatory_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
      <p>In the <uicontrol>Load Form</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Before Save</uicontrol> events, from the drop-down list of <uicontrol>Set Value of</uicontrol> field, you can select the field name for which the default value must be set, and then update the value in the adjacent field.<ul>
            <li outputclass="break_avoid">If the selected field name is a text box field type, then  a text box is created adjacent to the selected field.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Set_textbox_field_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li outputclass="break_avoid">If the selected field name is a drop-down list with a defined
list of values, then a drop-down list is created adjacent to the selected field.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Set_drop-down_field_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
